NAME

    Syntax::Feature::In - provides an "in" operator as a replacement for
    smartmatch

VERSION

    version 0.0003

SYNOPSIS

        use syntax 'in';
    
        my $found = 42 |in| [ 1 .. 100 ];

DESCRIPTION

    This modules imports the in operator. It can be used as in infix
    operator:

        $foo |in| $bar

    Or in a more traditional way:

        in->($foo, $bar)

    It does a simplified version of smartmatch as described in
    match::simple.

SEE ALSO

      * match::simple

      * Scalar::In

